text:
Vice presidential debates are typically forgotten by the next sunrise. But that’s not going to be the case this year, when voters can easily envision either @Mike_Pence or @KamalaHarris having to step into the top spot.

name: sfchronicle
text:
Some Bay Area Safeway and Albertsons stores will offer at-home coronavirus test kits starting Monday. The saliva tests cost $139.99 each and will offer results within 72 hours through a partnership with Phosphorus Diagnostics. 
For the latest, follow here:
https://t.co/C5MHX6frQb

name: sfchronicle
text:
The Zogg Fire has burned 56,305 acres in Shasta County and is 80% contained. Fire officials warned that “fuels remain very receptive to ignition” due to the hot and dry temperatures over the past two months.

Follow our live updates for more:
https://t.co/g0p432uMiF

name: sfchronicle
text: Aaron Pryor was a star running back for Skyline High School. His coach had hoped football could help the 16-year-old escape East Oakland, which has suffered a recent spike in homicides, but the pandemic put him on the wrong track. https://t.co/dwsJhlH8DT

name: sfchronicle
text: With 2,774 fire-fighting personnel making use of 408 fire engines to fight the #GlassFire, “we are the priority for the state here,” division chief Ben Nicholls of Cal Fire said Monday during Sonoma County's daily update on the sprawling two-county blaze. https://t.co/0a6DSDEcnX
